<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="54" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,441,865]" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,477,502]" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
A 
<taxonomicName box="[368,496,477,502]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Trechisibus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[368,496,477,502]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">Trechisibus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species 
<quantity box="[605,774,478,502]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.11" metricValueMax="3.24" metricValueMin="2.98" pageId="5" pageNumber="54" unit="mm" value="3.11" valueMax="3.24" valueMin="2.98">2.98–3.24 mm</quantity>
long, dark brown, moderately shiny; elytra with apex, marginal border and sutural interval lighter brown; legs, antennae and mouth parts reddish-brown. Hind angles of pronotum nearly right or scarcely obtuse. Elytra oval, not depressed on disc, with one setigerous puncture on 3rd stria at about 1/3 from base. Due to the peculiar median lobe of aedeagus with hook shaped apex, 
<taxonomicName box="[1254,1365,589,612]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Trechisibus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="recuayi" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[1254,1365,589,612]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">T. recuayi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1372,1436,588,613]" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1372,1436,588,613]" pageId="5" pageNumber="54" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
may be confused with two other species living in Cordillera Blanca (
<taxonomicName authority="Etonti &amp; Mateu, 1992" authorityName="Etonti &amp; Mateu" authorityYear="1992" box="[924,1388,624,649]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Trechisibus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lamasi">
<emphasis box="[924,1135,624,649]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">Trechisibus lamasi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Etonti" box="[1141,1388,624,649]" pageId="5" pageNumber="54" refString="Etonti, M. &amp; Mateu, J. (1992) Sette nuovi Trechinae del Peru (Coleoptera, Carabidae). Bollettino del Museo civico di Storia naturale di Venezia, 41, 109 - 130." type="journal article" year="1992">Etonti &amp; Mateu, 1992</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Allegro, Giachino &amp; Sciaky, 2008" authorityName="Allegro, Giachino &amp; Sciaky" authorityYear="2008" box="[151,775,660,685]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Trechisibus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="decensii">
<emphasis box="[151,378,660,685]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">Trechisibus decensii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Allegro" box="[386,775,660,685]" pageId="5" pageNumber="54" refString="Allegro, G., Giachino, P. M. &amp; Sciaky, R. (2008) Notes on some Trechini (Coleoptera Carabidae) of South America with description of new species from Chile, Ecuador and Peru. In: Giachino, P. M. (Ed.), Biodiversity of South America, I. Memoirs on Biodiversity 1. World Biodiversity Association Onlus, Verona, Italy, pp. 131 - 171." type="journal article" year="2008">Allegro, Giachino &amp; Sciaky, 2008</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
), which also share a very similar external morphology, but it the can be easily distinguished by the smaller size and by a shorter and more stumpy median lobe of aedeagus, with differently shaped copulatory piece (
<figureCitation box="[618,687,732,757]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1982,2004]" captionTargetBox="[292,1275,213,1934]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[272,1305,193,1948]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Median lobe of aedeagus of the ‘ Trechisibus lamasi group’ species: T. lamasi Etonti &amp; Mateu, 1992 (a); T. recuayi n. sp. HT (b); T. decensii Allegro, Giachino &amp; Sciaky, 2008 HT (c)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/256753/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
